folder: Henry Street & Middagh Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Henry Street, at the N.E. corner of Middagh Street, showing a 2-story building, used at various intervals as a meat market, and as a central distributing point for ice.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Middagh Street & Henry Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Middagh Street, west of Henry Street, showing in the foreground, the Assumption Parochial School, under the Jurisdiction of the parish by that name, with the rectory on the south side ot the street, and farther westward.
I the background, appear sky-scrapers of lower Manhattan.
April 16, 1936.
